org.openbel.framework.ws.core
Class Cache<T extends Cacheable>

java.lang.Object
  org.openbel.framework.ws.core.Cache<T>

public class Cache<T extends Cacheable>
extends Object

A Cache object is a hashmap with values wrapped around in soft references. Objects held by the hashmap will be cleared when garbage collector has determined it needs to reclaim the memory.

Author:
tchu

public void put(T value)

Adds an object to cache. Key for this cache entry is determined by Cacheable.getCacheKey() There is no guarantee that this object will be there by the time the next get(key) is called.

put

public void put(T value,
                long timeToClearMins)
         throws CacheException
Adds an object to cache. There is no guarantee that this object will be there by the time the next get(key) is called. If no other references are pointing to the cached object, the supplied value are guaranteed to be removed from cache after timeToClearMins + 1 minutes.
